WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.240 --> 00:00:06.080
Search has finally evolved and now everyone wants&nbsp;
to rank in AI search. But how? Our brilliant team&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:06.080 --> 00:00:12.720
at HRF studied 75,000 brands and 25 million AI&nbsp;
overviews and found five key factors that give&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:12.720 --> 00:00:18.800
you the best chance of ranking in AI search with&nbsp;
GEO. And it all starts with branded mentions.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:18.800 --> 00:00:24.400
Large language models like chatbt and Google learn&nbsp;
by reading the web. And every time your brand name&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:24.400 --> 00:00:30.400
appears on a credible site, that becomes another&nbsp;
training example. And the more often an LLM sees&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:35.520
your brand connected to a specific topic, the&nbsp;
more confidently it associates your name with&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:35.520 --> 00:00:40.960
that subject when generating answers. It's like&nbsp;
when you hear Red Bull, you think extreme sports.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:40.960 --> 00:00:46.480
Or when you hear Tesla, you think electric cars.&nbsp;
Or when you think of Ahrefs, you think of Sam O,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:46.480 --> 00:00:52.320
the charismatic SEO beast. Branded mentions are so&nbsp;
important that they have the strongest correlation&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:52.320 --> 00:00:58.640
with visibility in Google's AI overviews. higher&nbsp;
than back links, referring domains, and domain&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:58.640 --> 00:01:04.320
rating. But how do we know which pages or sites&nbsp;
to get mentioned on? According to our research,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:04.320 --> 00:01:09.200
get mentioned on highly linked to pages if you&nbsp;
want to rank in Google AI overviews and high&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:09.200 --> 00:01:15.120
traffic pages if you want more visibility in chat&nbsp;
GPT and perplexity. To find pages and websites&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:15.120 --> 00:01:20.720
worth getting mentioned on, go to HF's brand&nbsp;
radar and enter your brand, competitors, brands,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:20.720 --> 00:01:25.840
niche, and run the search. Then hit the cited&nbsp;
domains report where you'll see the top websites,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:25.840 --> 00:01:31.600
the number of AI responses, and the exact number&nbsp;
of times each brand is getting mentioned and how&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:31.600 --> 00:01:36.000
they're being mentioned. From here, you can join&nbsp;
the Reddit threads AI is pulling from. Reach&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:42.000
out to YouTubers for future reviews or contact&nbsp;
publishers for potential PR campaigns. Basically,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:47.520
you want your brand to appear literally everywhere&nbsp;
online, ideally in a positive and topically&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:47.520 --> 00:01:53.440
relevant way. And that's because of the second key&nbsp;
factor for ranking an AI search. Longtail queries.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:53.440 --> 00:01:58.800
In traditional SEO, targeting longtail keywords&nbsp;
was mostly about coverage. The more queries you&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:58.800 --> 00:02:04.320
rank for, the more ways there are for searchers&nbsp;
to find you. But in AI search, longtail queries&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:04.320 --> 00:02:10.880
play a different role. AI assistants like Chat GPT&nbsp;
may actually use them to decide who to recommend.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:10.880 --> 00:02:14.800
And it's because of how AI assistants&nbsp;
work. When someone enters a prompt like,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:14.800 --> 00:02:21.120
"Plan me a 5-day trip to Japan in November," the&nbsp;
AI assistant fans it out into dozens of smaller&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:21.120 --> 00:02:26.800
longtail subqueries. They then pull information&nbsp;
from multiple sources across the web and combine&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:26.800 --> 00:02:32.960
it into one complete answer. So, if your content&nbsp;
ranks for those niche specific queries, your brand&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:32.960 --> 00:02:38.640
has a much better chance of being included in the&nbsp;
AI's final response. And our data backs that up,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:38.640 --> 00:02:44.480
showing that Google's AI overviews are way more&nbsp;
likely to appear on longer niche queries. So from&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:44.480 --> 00:02:49.920
a practical standpoint, you should a create&nbsp;
content that answers more complex specific&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:49.920 --> 00:02:58.320
questions and b content clusters that deeply cover&nbsp;
the full depth of a topic. But here's the twist.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:58.320 --> 00:03:04.160
Even if you've nailed all of this, it might not&nbsp;
matter. Because if your content isn't structured&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:04.160 --> 00:03:10.240
the way AI assistants process information, you may&nbsp;
not get as many AI search mentions as you should&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:10.240 --> 00:03:15.280
be getting. One way Google AI reads content&nbsp;
is by using a tree walking algorithm, meaning&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:15.280 --> 00:03:22.160
it follows the exact semantic HTML structure of a&nbsp;
web page from top to bottom. And this makes well-&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:22.160 --> 00:03:27.600
formatted and structured content easier for it&nbsp;
to process. But it's not just about using heading&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:27.600 --> 00:03:33.280
tags and bulleted lists. It's about how your&nbsp;
information flows. Your content should be clear,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:33.280 --> 00:03:39.600
organized, and easy to follow. And this matters&nbsp;
because when Google or Chat GPT read your page,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:39.600 --> 00:03:45.600
they don't process it all at once. They chunk&nbsp;
your content into smaller pieces, almost like&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:45.600 --> 00:03:51.280
reading it paragraph by paragraph, and then they&nbsp;
decide which parts are most useful to keep. So,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:51.280 --> 00:03:56.480
if your juiciest points are buried deep&nbsp;
down or mixed into long, messy sections,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:56.480 --> 00:04:02.320
it makes it less efficient for AI to process your&nbsp;
content, which may have a role in rankings. Now,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:02.320 --> 00:04:07.200
that doesn't mean you should start writing&nbsp;
in short, choppy blurbs like an FAQ or make&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:07.200 --> 00:04:13.200
every paragraph its own idea. Instead, focus on&nbsp;
grouping related thoughts together and keeping&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:13.200 --> 00:04:18.800
each section focused on a single takeaway.&nbsp;
Think of it like giving AI a clear outline&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:18.800 --> 00:04:24.320
where each part should make sense on its own&nbsp;
but still naturally connect to the next. Now,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:24.320 --> 00:04:28.800
even if your content is perfectly written and&nbsp;
structured, there's another key factor that&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:28.800 --> 00:04:34.960
can put you in or completely knock you out of AI&nbsp;
results. And our data shows that this key factor&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:34.960 --> 00:04:41.680
is all about freshness. Our study of 17 million&nbsp;
citations across seven AI search platforms found&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:41.680 --> 00:04:47.520
that AI assistants strongly prefer newer&nbsp;
information. In fact, content cited by AI&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:47.520 --> 00:04:53.760
is 25.7% fresher than the content that shows&nbsp;
up in regular Google results. And Chat GPT and&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:53.760 --> 00:04:59.200
Perplexity go even further. They tend to list&nbsp;
citations from newest to oldest. That happens&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:59.200 --> 00:05:04.720
because most assistants use something called rag.&nbsp;
RAG stands for retrieval, augment, and generation,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:04.720 --> 00:05:10.160
which is the part of an AI system that goes out&nbsp;
and looks things up. If a model already knows the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:10.160 --> 00:05:14.560
answer from its training data, it doesn't need&nbsp;
to search again. Just like you and I don't need&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:14.560 --> 00:05:20.240
to search for directions to places we visit all&nbsp;
the time. But if the topic is new or evolving,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:20.240 --> 00:05:25.280
Rag steps in and fetches the latest information&nbsp;
from the web to fill in the gaps. That's why&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:25.280 --> 00:05:30.800
freshness isn't just a ranking signal anymore.&nbsp;
It's a retrieval signal in this AI era. And here's&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:30.800 --> 00:05:36.000
proof that freshness can boost your AI rankings.&nbsp;
In April this year, HubSpot updated their small&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:41.600
business ideas article and soon saw a massive&nbsp;
spike to their organic traffic. No surprises&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:41.600 --> 00:05:49.040
there, but their AI mentions to that page also&nbsp;
spiked at the exact same time, generating over,00&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:49.040 --> 00:05:54.160
new mentions according to HR brand radar. So&nbsp;
something you can do is to take note of pages&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:54.160 --> 00:05:59.600
that could benefit from regular updates and add&nbsp;
them to your regular refresh cycle. Update facts,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:59.600 --> 00:06:04.160
new quotes or stats, remove things that have&nbsp;
become irrelevant, and redate the post when&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:04.160 --> 00:06:08.720
it's meaningful. And that one small update could&nbsp;
be the difference in getting mentioned across&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:08.720 --> 00:06:12.880
AI platforms. By the way, I probably should&nbsp;
have mentioned this earlier, but before you&nbsp;&nbsp;

